{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/dry-eye-syndrome/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"25984af0-631e-5b5e-8366-c2a6a53ffce8","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 6a07acb7-bb1a-4716-bdd5-a7f2018898eb --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 6a07acb7-bb1a-4716-bdd5-a7f2018898eb -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item cebc5a25-b183-4bf5-9906-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field ea746730-6800-4b91-870b-a7f2018898eb --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field ea746730-6800-4b91-870b-a7f2018898eb --><!-- begin field 5e9082ed-69b2-4ecf-b343-a7f2018898eb --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 5e9082ed-69b2-4ecf-b343-a7f2018898eb --><!-- begin field e4d64ff9-953e-4ce4-a348-a7f2018898eb --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field e4d64ff9-953e-4ce4-a348-a7f2018898eb --><!-- begin field 2f037113-786b-4dfa-a993-a7f2018898eb --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 2f037113-786b-4dfa-a993-a7f2018898eb --><!-- begin field d206343e-797c-43d7-b2de-a7f2018898eb --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field d206343e-797c-43d7-b2de-a7f2018898eb --><!-- begin field c5031c2e-a65d-4150-9b97-a7f2018898eb --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field c5031c2e-a65d-4150-9b97-a7f2018898eb --><!-- end item cebc5a25-b183-4bf5-9906-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"386fd023-80c8-5773-9545-27347387cc3b","topicId":"19fd4567-edfc-4646-8106-bd391e9fc519","topicName":"Dry eye syndrome","slug":"dry-eye-syndrome","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2017","chapters":[{"id":"82582060-8b99-5c66-9fef-320feddcfce7","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"4d65393d-c49d-5d93-97eb-529b725441ec","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"fdb881a7-0683-51f6-bf90-e722245af767","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"0c07d88f-cc23-5753-8b62-acea5a2111b8","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"9590a4e4-d362-599d-b9b5-f38d9282b1d0","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"dfd74917-3fbf-5b2b-9def-21fcdbfd6143","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"54ce9280-6602-5b59-9353-0f274bb0b830","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"1b6213cb-be33-529a-ad0b-b254fa0e8f36","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"6febc8d3-da2c-5312-b77b-a81a02506f5f","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit